## Project Structure

```
ai-saas-copilot/
├── backend/
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── github_auth.py     # OAuth flow + GitHub API proxy
│   │   ├── analytics.py       # Risk scores, cost waste, dormant repos
│   │   ├── security.py        # Security findings + name-pattern detection
│   │   ├── ai.py              # AI recommendation generation
│   │   └── actions.py         # Jira / Slack / Email / Archive action endpoints
│   ├── agents/
│   │   └── repository_agent.py  # Recommendation logic (rule-based + LLM-ready)
│   ├── models/                # SQLAlchemy ORM models
│   ├── services/
│   │   └── github_service.py  # GitHub REST API client
│   ├── db/                    # Database connection + session
│   └── main.py                # FastAPI app, CORS, middleware
│
└── frontend/
    └── src/
        ├── App.tsx              # Routing + OAuth callback handler
        ├── pages/
        │   ├── Dashboard.tsx    # Main dashboard (all tabs + AI chat)
        │   └── ConnectGithub.tsx  # Landing / login page
        └── services/
            └── api.ts           # Typed fetch wrapper (credentials: include)
```

---

## Demo Mode

Don't want to connect a real GitHub account? Add `?demo=true` to the URL:

```
http://localhost:5173/?demo=true
```

This loads a set of realistic mock repositories without touching any real data.

---

## Roadmap

The action buttons (Jira, Slack, Email, Archive) currently demonstrate the UI flow with mock responses. Real integrations are straightforward to wire in:

| Action | What to add |
|--------|-------------|
| **Create Jira ticket** | Jira REST API — `POST /rest/api/3/issue` with an API token |
| **Notify Slack** | Slack Incoming Webhooks — one `POST` to a webhook URL |
| **Send Email** | SendGrid or AWS SES — `POST /v3/mail/send` |
| **Archive repo** | GitHub API — `PATCH /repos/{owner}/{repo}` with `{"archived": true}` |

Other planned improvements:
- Replace in-memory `_pending_tokens` with Redis (TTL = 5 min) for production safety
- Add org selector on the dashboard — currently defaults to personal repos
- Scheduled background sync (Celery or APScheduler) so data stays fresh without manual reload
- Wire `repository_agent.py` back to an LLM (GPT-4 or Gemini — commented code already exists)

---

## Environment Variables Reference

**Backend (`backend/.env`)**

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `GITHUB_CLIENT_ID` | GitHub OAuth App client ID |
| `GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET` | GitHub OAuth App client secret |
| `DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL connection string |
| `FRONTEND_URL` | Frontend origin for CORS + redirect (default: `http://localhost:5173`) |
| `SESSION_SECRET` | Secret key for Starlette session middleware |
| `ALERT_RECIPIENTS` | Comma-separated email list for mock email action (default: `security@company.com,ops@company.com`) |

**Frontend (`frontend/.env`)**

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `VITE_API_URL` | Backend base URL (default: `http://localhost:8000`) |

